<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-03-04T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-03-04T14:00:00-05:00" n="628" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.918/53: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-04T14:00:00-05:00">March 4, 1930—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>82. Referring to Canton’s telegrams February 28, 1 p.m., and March 1,
                            noon. Department approves as appropriate under the circumstances action
                            taken by the American Consul General in reference to the reported desire
                            of the Chinese authorities to expel Lyon. Department asks that Legation
                            reply to Canton’s telegrams and report any further developments.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
